  "instructions": "<p>Great place for knights level 80+ to get experience. Usually it's waste but if you get lucky you can profit.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>‚öîÔ∏è<strong> Strategy</strong></p>\n<p>Right at the entrance, there will be many creatures, so don't despair. Basically you will do a loop counterwiseclock.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Bring firebombs üî• to control the number of creatures that will attack you. If you are not used to this place, start with 3 creatures.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Vile Grandmaster is the most annoying with a big damage and regeneration, so always focus on it.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>In the south area there can be 2 Vile Grandmasters and 2 Renegade Knights. If that's the case, kill one Renegade Knight and go back. Two grandmasters are very hard to block in this level and can kill you.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>üõ°Ô∏è<strong> Equipments</strong></p>\n<p>Overall you don't need special equipments here, except for Werewolf Amulet, that gives much defense against this creatures and is a game changer here.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Melee rings (axe/club/sword) help a lot, especially if your skill is not good.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>‚öóÔ∏è<strong> Imbuements</strong></p>\n<p>Intricate Vampirism and Intricate Mana Void.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>üíØ<strong> Prey</strong></p>\n<p>If there is def/attack prey for Vile Grandmaster, that must be prioritized, else, focus on XP prey.</p>",
